Well Lew,<br><br>
You have gone an done it again.  Chastise a man for not being in two places at once.  If your previous posts are accurate, this is the current situation.  You claim to be one of the 98% of the Vets who don’t have our problems.  An informed individual of the war effort.  Now Lew which is it, did you take notes while you were a soldier or while you were a protester?  Your answer obviously would be I was both places and as such know both sides.  If not you just lied.  Logic is tough.  I would never be so shallow to believe that a man doesn’t have the life expectancy and capability to experience more than one situation in his life.  I would not even make that assumption of you.<br><br>
Cook was a one tour man and then returned to the states to continue his education and then become a career LA police officer during the height of the protest movement.  He had to be involved in all the dirt.  I can say without much question much more qualified than you.  For all we know he may have busted one of your friends, but we know that isn’t true.  Right Lew?<br><br>
I am with Jed.  If you have something of substance to contribute I would like to read it.  If not just watch and learn.  I am not here to tolerate your diatribe nor is anyone else.  I read and digest every word that Jed posts.  I will say there are many things that we don’t agree on.  He posts with eloquence, confidence and conviction and does not apologize for his convictions.  A right any man should have.  I am content to read this exchange and have no desire to force my opinions because others are doing an adequate job of debate.<br><br>
You on the other hand are trying to be a square peg in a round hole and doing a good job of it.  You just don’t fit.  I do not advocate shutting anyone out but the choice is yours.  Participate or be silent.  At least have respect for yourself if not for the others.<br>

